%N A397874 Decimal expansion of the large face angle, in radians, of a canonical (dual-uniform) heptagonal trapezohedron.
%C A397874 The heptagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the heptagonal antiprism.
%C A397874 Its faces are kites with one acute angle (A397873) and three obtuse angles (this constant).
%H A397874 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397874/b397874.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397874 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HeptagonalTrapezohedron.html">Heptagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397874 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Heptagonal_antitegum">Heptagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397874 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397874 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A397874 Equals arccos(1/2 - cos(Pi/7)) = arccos(1/2 - A073052).
%F A397874 Equals arccos(c), where c = -0.40096... is the smallest root of 8*x^3 - 8*x^2 - 2*x + 1.
%e A397874 1.98337053857976354089701182929655613224927670815...
%t A397874 First[RealDigits[ArcCos[1/2 - Cos[Pi/7]], 10, 100]]
%o A397874 (PARI) acos(1/2-cos(Pi/7)) \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jul 20 2026
